{"body": "I confirmed with the Rails Core team and the `form_tag` without block should not generate the closing tag. This is intentional and documented. The documentation says that it starts the form tag and the block version is an exception to this behavior.\r\n\r\nThis is similar with `File.open` that closes the file if you pass a block, but not close it without the block.\r\n\r\nAlso I discussed about the change in the vendor code and they said that we don't need to accept it because the change is to identify the `form_tag` possible issue.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9338215", "created_at": "2012-10-11T12:38:33Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7901#issuecomment-9338215", "updated_at": "2012-10-11T12:38:33Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7901, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rafaelfranca", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2c7b84fa30f0cea96a90729afe2970a0.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "rafaelfranca", "type": "User", "id": 47848, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f7cfbd3543c15100b12d"}, "id": 9338215, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails